    <h1>How to Grow Your Business Online in 2025 ‚Äî Simple Steps for Beginners</h1>
    <div class="meta">Published: <time datetime="2025-10-09">October 9, 2025</time> ¬∑ by AdDev Studio</div>

    <p>In 2025, people discover products and services on Google and social media first. You don‚Äôt need a complex website or a big budget to start. You need a clean page, clear information, and consistency. Here‚Äôs a simple plan.</p>

    <h2>1) Build a simple, fast website</h2>
    <p>Keep it light: one homepage, services, contact. Clear headings, short paragraphs, and a visible call-to-action like ‚ÄúContact us‚Äù. Fast pages mean happier visitors and better rankings.</p>

    <h2>2) Set up basic SEO</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Write a clear title (what you do + city/area).</li>
      <li>Add a short meta description (why choose you).</li>
      <li>Use headings (H1, H2) and descriptive URLs.</li>
      <li>Compress images and avoid heavy scripts.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3) Publish helpful content weekly</h2>
    <p>Answer real questions your customers ask. One article per week is enough to start. Over time, this brings steady organic traffic.</p>

    <div class="box"><strong>Idea starter:</strong> ‚ÄúHow much does a basic website cost?‚Äù or ‚ÄúWhat is local SEO and why does it matter?‚Äù</div>

    <h2>4) Make it easy to contact you</h2>
    <p>Show a phone number, email, and WhatsApp. Add opening hours and a clear location area. The goal is trust and quick action.</p>

    <h2>5) Track and improve</h2>
    <p>Use simple analytics to see what pages people read. Improve titles, add FAQs, and keep the site fast. Small improvements every week compound over time.</p>

